{"id":14881290,"mediaExerciseId":"b4709392-d53d-47f1-8e7b-d7d3fd16c46a","exerciseName":"5","chapterName":"11","chapterTitle":"Project Analysis and Evaluation","groupId":612351,"groupTitle":"Critical Thinking Questions","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":375,"solutions":[{"id":6059202,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"As we may recall, degree of operating leverage is the measure of a company's income relative to their fixed costs. \n\nIn an airline, the fixed costs are very high since the maintenance of the airplanes, fuel, as well as salary of the crew are also high. This means that the room for profit is lower since they have high fixed costs. \n\nMoreover, an industry with high degree of operating leverage can experience massive changes in their income even with very small alterations in their fixed costs. ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1}],"rating":0,"solutionUuid":"3784d64c-7e8b-4993-a34f-5b9ee014a7e2","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":1}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14881291,"exerciseName":"6","page":375,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"2d51f7dd-6b18-428d-a8b1-c28fc026f0a9","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook